    • Field Detail

      • formula1

        private String formula1
        Formula of one of the groups whose dihedral angle is being measured. May be a ChemAxon-defined shortcut group, or may be a SMILES representation with the 1st atom counting as the attachment point.

      • formula2

        private String formula2
        Formula of the other group whose dihedral angle is being measured. May be a ChemAxon-defined shortcut group, or may be a SMILES representation with the 1st atom counting as the attachment point.

      • groupRelationship

        private int groupRelationship
        Nature of dihedral angle: anti, gauche, etc.

      • populateLists

        private void populateLists(Molecule mol,

                           Molecule groupMol1,
                           Molecule groupMol2)
        Populate two atom lists with attachment points of group1 and group2, respectively, that are attached to an atom of the bond about which the dihedral angle is being measured.
        Parameters:
        mol - the molecule
        mappedAtom - atom of the bond about which the dihedral angle is being measured
        ligListG1 - a list of atoms that are attached to the bond atom and are the attachment points of groupMol1
        ligListG2 - a list of atoms that are attached to the bond atom and are the attachment points of groupMol2
        groupMol1 - molecule of a group whose dihedral angle is being measured
        groupMol2 - molecule of the other group whose dihedral angle is being measured
